25|$|The {{two main}} policy {{responses}} {{to global warming}} are to reduce greenhouse gas emissions (<b>climate</b> <b>change</b> <b>mitigation)</b> and {{to adapt to the}} impacts of global warming (e.g., by building levees in response to sea level rise). Another policy response which has recently received greater attention is geoengineering of the climate system (e.g. injecting aerosols into the atmosphere to reflect sunlight away from the Earth's surface).|$|E
