25|$|Wetlands {{provide an}} {{astonishing}} array of ecosystem {{services for the}} local community. These include mitigating the effects of flood and drought, replenishing groundwater, helping filter sediment and nutrients and purify water, providing reservoirs of biodiversity and wetland resources, providing for cultural values, recreation and tourism, and <b>climate</b> <b>change</b> <b>mitigation</b> and adaptation. The Lower Waikato-Waipa Flood Protection Scheme has been estimated to save the Waikato Region $5.2 million (in 2007 dollars) by limiting damage to surrounding farmland during times of peak flood events.|$|E
